        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 5:43PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 543 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Theo, or near Big Hill Pond State Park, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Forty Forks, Selmer, Good Hope, Bethel Springs, Pebble Hill,
Eastview, Wenasoga, Guys, Old Lawton, Theo, Ramer, Purdy, Chewalla,
Hickory Flats, Mount Vinson, New Lawton, Martin Camp, Caffey,
Crumtown, and Gift.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for northeastern
Mississippi...and west Tennessee.</instruction>
